<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="433" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,345,660]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,345,371]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kamiya" authorityYear="1963" box="[280,440,346,372]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Axinoscymnus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[280,440,346,372]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Axinoscymnus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Vandenberg, 2004" authorityName="Vandenberg" authorityYear="2004" box="[584,957,346,372]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Sasajiscymnus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[584,747,346,372]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Sasajiscymnus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Vandenberg, N. J." box="[754,957,346,372]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" pagination="483 - 484" refId="ref17073" refString="Vandenberg, N. J. (2004) Homonymy in the Coccinellidae (Coleoptera), or something fishy about Pseudoscymnus Chapin. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 106 (2), 483 - 484." type="journal article" year="2004">
Vandenberg, 
<quantity box="[901,957,346,372]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.090159999999999" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" unit="in" value="2004.0">2004</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in having three tarsomere tarsi (
<figureCitation box="[1316,1398,346,373]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[151,1418,684,1901]" captionTargetId="figure-170@2.[151,1436,684,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Main characters of the genus Axinoscymnus Kamiya: a–h Axinoscymnus pingxiangicus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a head b prothorax, ventral view c prothorax, frontal view d hind leg e labium f antenna g maxilla h mandible i–j Axinoscymnus beneficus Kamiya, 1963: i spermatheca j coxites. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651159" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651159/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Fig. 1d</figureCitation>
). It can be also easily distinguished from the other genera belonging to the tribe 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peng &amp; Xie &amp; Peng &amp; Wang &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2022" box="[994,1101,382,408]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Scymnini">Scymnini</taxonomicName>
by the following combination of characters: eyes large with a correspondingly narrow frons (
<figureCitation box="[873,955,418,444]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[151,1418,684,1901]" captionTargetId="figure-170@2.[151,1436,684,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Main characters of the genus Axinoscymnus Kamiya: a–h Axinoscymnus pingxiangicus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a head b prothorax, ventral view c prothorax, frontal view d hind leg e labium f antenna g maxilla h mandible i–j Axinoscymnus beneficus Kamiya, 1963: i spermatheca j coxites. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651159" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651159/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Fig. 1a</figureCitation>
); antennae composed of 11 antennomeres (
<figureCitation box="[160,236,454,481]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[151,1418,684,1901]" captionTargetId="figure-170@2.[151,1436,684,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Main characters of the genus Axinoscymnus Kamiya: a–h Axinoscymnus pingxiangicus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a head b prothorax, ventral view c prothorax, frontal view d hind leg e labium f antenna g maxilla h mandible i–j Axinoscymnus beneficus Kamiya, 1963: i spermatheca j coxites. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651159" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651159/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Fig. 1f</figureCitation>
); maxillary palpi weakly securiform (
<figureCitation box="[656,737,454,480]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[151,1418,684,1901]" captionTargetId="figure-170@2.[151,1436,684,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Main characters of the genus Axinoscymnus Kamiya: a–h Axinoscymnus pingxiangicus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a head b prothorax, ventral view c prothorax, frontal view d hind leg e labium f antenna g maxilla h mandible i–j Axinoscymnus beneficus Kamiya, 1963: i spermatheca j coxites. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651159" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651159/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[707,737,454,480]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" unit="g" value="1.0">1g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
); prosternum in front of procoxae very short (
<figureCitation box="[1246,1326,454,481]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[151,1418,684,1901]" captionTargetId="figure-170@2.[151,1436,684,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Main characters of the genus Axinoscymnus Kamiya: a–h Axinoscymnus pingxiangicus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a head b prothorax, ventral view c prothorax, frontal view d hind leg e labium f antenna g maxilla h mandible i–j Axinoscymnus beneficus Kamiya, 1963: i spermatheca j coxites. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651159" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651159/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Fig. 1b</figureCitation>
), narrowly carinate, less than half width of procoxal cavity, subtrapezoidal (
<figureCitation box="[907,1022,490,517]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[151,1418,684,1901]" captionTargetId="figure-170@2.[151,1436,684,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Main characters of the genus Axinoscymnus Kamiya: a–h Axinoscymnus pingxiangicus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a head b prothorax, ventral view c prothorax, frontal view d hind leg e labium f antenna g maxilla h mandible i–j Axinoscymnus beneficus Kamiya, 1963: i spermatheca j coxites. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651159" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651159/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Figs 1b–c</figureCitation>
); mesoventrite strongly convex (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1976,2000]" captionTargetBox="[169,1413,1069,1935]" captionTargetId="figure-345@20.[156,1431,1054,1953]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 13. Axinoscymnus pingxiangicus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651198" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651198/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Fig. 13b</figureCitation>
); abdominal postcoxal lines complete (
<figureCitation box="[642,740,526,553]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1976,2000]" captionTargetBox="[169,1413,1069,1935]" captionTargetId="figure-345@20.[156,1431,1054,1953]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 13. Axinoscymnus pingxiangicus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651198" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651198/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Fig. 13d</figureCitation>
); abdomen with five ventrites (
<figureCitation box="[1097,1196,526,553]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1976,2000]" captionTargetBox="[169,1413,1069,1935]" captionTargetId="figure-345@20.[156,1431,1054,1953]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 13. Axinoscymnus pingxiangicus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651198" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651198/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Fig. 13d</figureCitation>
); penis short without penis capsule (
<figureCitation box="[317,412,562,588]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1976,2000]" captionTargetBox="[169,1413,1069,1935]" captionTargetId="figure-345@20.[156,1431,1054,1953]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 13. Axinoscymnus pingxiangicus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651198" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651198/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Fig. 13e</figureCitation>
), and elongate coxites of female (
<figureCitation box="[790,865,562,589]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[151,1418,684,1901]" captionTargetId="figure-170@2.[151,1436,684,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Main characters of the genus Axinoscymnus Kamiya: a–h Axinoscymnus pingxiangicus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a head b prothorax, ventral view c prothorax, frontal view d hind leg e labium f antenna g maxilla h mandible i–j Axinoscymnus beneficus Kamiya, 1963: i spermatheca j coxites. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651159" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651159/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Fig. 1j</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="434" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,345,660]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,597,623]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Description.</emphasis>
Body oval or elongate oval, moderately convex, dorsum densely pubescent, widest around middle of elytra.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651159" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6651159" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651159/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" startId="2.[151,250,1944,1968]" targetBox="[151,1418,684,1901]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1944,2040]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,277,1944,1968]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">FIGURE 1.</emphasis>
Main characters of the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Kamiya" authorityName="Kamiya" authorityYear="1963" box="[595,832,1944,1968]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Axinoscymnus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
