<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,1113]" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">
Head transverse; frons relatively narrow (
<figureCitation box="[679,761,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[151,1418,684,1901]" captionTargetId="figure-170@2.[151,1436,684,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Main characters of the genus Axinoscymnus Kamiya: a–h Axinoscymnus pingxiangicus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a head b prothorax, ventral view c prothorax, frontal view d hind leg e labium f antenna g maxilla h mandible i–j Axinoscymnus beneficus Kamiya, 1963: i spermatheca j coxites. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651159" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651159/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">Fig. 1a</figureCitation>
), slightly convex. Eyes large, inner ocular margin arcuate. Clypeus short, anterior margin of clypeus straight. Antennae composed of 11 antennomeres (
<figureCitation box="[1191,1269,187,214]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[151,1418,684,1901]" captionTargetId="figure-170@2.[151,1436,684,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Main characters of the genus Axinoscymnus Kamiya: a–h Axinoscymnus pingxiangicus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a head b prothorax, ventral view c prothorax, frontal view d hind leg e labium f antenna g maxilla h mandible i–j Axinoscymnus beneficus Kamiya, 1963: i spermatheca j coxites. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651159" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651159/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">Fig. 1f</figureCitation>
); antennomere 1 stout, cylindrical, longer than wide; base of the antennomere 2 slightly narrower than antennomere 1, as long as antennomere 1, curved and distinctly rounded on inner side; antennomere 3 relatively slender, base narrowed; antennomeres 4 and 5 subequal to antennomere 
<quantity box="[700,744,295,321]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.62" pageId="3" pageNumber="434" unit="in" value="3.0">3 in</quantity>
length and width; antennomere 6 slightly shorter than antennomere 5; antennomere 7 trapezoidal, apical part wider than base; antennomere 8 to 11 forming a fusiform club, the terminal antennomere small, distinctly narrower and shorter than penultimate one (
<figureCitation box="[1072,1149,367,394]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[151,1418,684,1901]" captionTargetId="figure-170@2.[151,1436,684,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Main characters of the genus Axinoscymnus Kamiya: a–h Axinoscymnus pingxiangicus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a head b prothorax, ventral view c prothorax, frontal view d hind leg e labium f antenna g maxilla h mandible i–j Axinoscymnus beneficus Kamiya, 1963: i spermatheca j coxites. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651159" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651159/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">Fig. 1f</figureCitation>
). Mandible bifid apically, with well-developed molar tooth (
<figureCitation box="[543,628,403,430]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[151,1418,684,1901]" captionTargetId="figure-170@2.[151,1436,684,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Main characters of the genus Axinoscymnus Kamiya: a–h Axinoscymnus pingxiangicus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a head b prothorax, ventral view c prothorax, frontal view d hind leg e labium f antenna g maxilla h mandible i–j Axinoscymnus beneficus Kamiya, 1963: i spermatheca j coxites. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651159" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651159/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">Fig. 1h</figureCitation>
). Maxillary palpus with four palpomeres (
<figureCitation box="[1118,1201,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[151,1418,684,1901]" captionTargetId="figure-170@2.[151,1436,684,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Main characters of the genus Axinoscymnus Kamiya: a–h Axinoscymnus pingxiangicus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a head b prothorax, ventral view c prothorax, frontal view d hind leg e labium f antenna g maxilla h mandible i–j Axinoscymnus beneficus Kamiya, 1963: i spermatheca j coxites. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651159" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651159/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[1172,1201,403,429]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="434" unit="g" value="1.0">1g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
), the basal one tiny, ring-like, the second one curved, outer margin distinctly longer than inner margin, the third one weakly broadened apically, outer margin twice as long as inner, the terminal palpomere stout, weakly securiform, apical margin weakly obliquely truncate. Labial palps with three palpomeres (
<figureCitation box="[778,858,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[151,1418,684,1901]" captionTargetId="figure-170@2.[151,1436,684,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Main characters of the genus Axinoscymnus Kamiya: a–h Axinoscymnus pingxiangicus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a head b prothorax, ventral view c prothorax, frontal view d hind leg e labium f antenna g maxilla h mandible i–j Axinoscymnus beneficus Kamiya, 1963: i spermatheca j coxites. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651159" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651159/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">Fig. 1e</figureCitation>
), terminal palpomere conical, narrower than penultimate one.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,1113]" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">
Pronotum moderately convex. Prosternum in front of procoxae very short (
<figureCitation box="[1068,1152,583,610]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[151,1418,684,1901]" captionTargetId="figure-170@2.[151,1436,684,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Main characters of the genus Axinoscymnus Kamiya: a–h Axinoscymnus pingxiangicus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a head b prothorax, ventral view c prothorax, frontal view d hind leg e labium f antenna g maxilla h mandible i–j Axinoscymnus beneficus Kamiya, 1963: i spermatheca j coxites. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651159" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651159/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">Fig. 1b</figureCitation>
), narrowly carinate, less than half width of procoxal cavity, subtrapezoidal (
<figureCitation box="[743,861,619,646]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[151,1418,684,1901]" captionTargetId="figure-170@2.[151,1436,684,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Main characters of the genus Axinoscymnus Kamiya: a–h Axinoscymnus pingxiangicus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a head b prothorax, ventral view c prothorax, frontal view d hind leg e labium f antenna g maxilla h mandible i–j Axinoscymnus beneficus Kamiya, 1963: i spermatheca j coxites. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651159" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651159/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">Figs 1b–c</figureCitation>
). Scutellar shield relatively small, triangular (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1976,2000]" captionTargetBox="[169,1413,1069,1935]" captionTargetId="figure-345@20.[156,1431,1054,1953]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 13. Axinoscymnus pingxiangicus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651198" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651198/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">Fig. 13a</figureCitation>
). Elytra at base slightly wider than pronotum, surface finely punctate. Humeri distinct. Lateral margins of elytra weakly arcuate, apex gently rounded. Elytral epipleuron narrow and nearly horizontal, terminated at level of hind coxae. Metaventrite strongly convex (
<figureCitation box="[575,672,727,754]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1976,2000]" captionTargetBox="[169,1413,1069,1935]" captionTargetId="figure-345@20.[156,1431,1054,1953]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 13. Axinoscymnus pingxiangicus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651198" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651198/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">Fig. 13b</figureCitation>
). Abdomen with five ventrites. Abdominal postcoxal lines recurved, complete (
<figureCitation box="[269,367,763,790]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1976,2000]" captionTargetBox="[169,1413,1069,1935]" captionTargetId="figure-345@20.[156,1431,1054,1953]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 13. Axinoscymnus pingxiangicus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651198" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651198/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">Fig. 13d</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,1113]" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">
Legs stout (
<figureCitation box="[333,416,799,826]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[151,1418,684,1901]" captionTargetId="figure-170@2.[151,1436,684,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Main characters of the genus Axinoscymnus Kamiya: a–h Axinoscymnus pingxiangicus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a head b prothorax, ventral view c prothorax, frontal view d hind leg e labium f antenna g maxilla h mandible i–j Axinoscymnus beneficus Kamiya, 1963: i spermatheca j coxites. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651159" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651159/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">Fig. 1d</figureCitation>
), not extending beyond external margin of elytra; femora of hind leg broad and flattened; tibiae without apical spurs; tarsus with three tarsomeres, basal and second tarsomeres lobed. Claws with sharp basal tooth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,1113]" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">
Male genitalia. relatively simple, penis short and slightly curved at the base, without processes of penis capsule (
<figureCitation box="[213,310,943,969]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1976,2000]" captionTargetBox="[169,1413,1069,1935]" captionTargetId="figure-345@20.[156,1431,1054,1953]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 13. Axinoscymnus pingxiangicus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651198" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651198/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">Fig. 13e</figureCitation>
); tegmen with penis guide and parameres stout and short, penis guide shorter than parameres (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1976,2000]" captionTargetBox="[169,1413,1069,1935]" captionTargetId="figure-345@20.[156,1431,1054,1953]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 13. Axinoscymnus pingxiangicus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651198" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651198/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">Fig. 13f–g</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,1113]" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">
Female genitalia. Coxites elongate, subtriangular, without styli (
<figureCitation box="[913,988,1015,1042]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[151,1418,684,1901]" captionTargetId="figure-170@2.[151,1436,684,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Main characters of the genus Axinoscymnus Kamiya: a–h Axinoscymnus pingxiangicus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a head b prothorax, ventral view c prothorax, frontal view d hind leg e labium f antenna g maxilla h mandible i–j Axinoscymnus beneficus Kamiya, 1963: i spermatheca j coxites. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651159" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651159/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">Fig. 1j</figureCitation>
). Spermatheca short and stout, bulbousshaped as shown on 
<figureCitation box="[381,457,1051,1077]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[151,1418,684,1901]" captionTargetId="figure-170@2.[151,1436,684,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Main characters of the genus Axinoscymnus Kamiya: a–h Axinoscymnus pingxiangicus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a head b prothorax, ventral view c prothorax, frontal view d hind leg e labium f antenna g maxilla h mandible i–j Axinoscymnus beneficus Kamiya, 1963: i spermatheca j coxites. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6651159" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6651159/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">Fig. 1i</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
